
AGILE AND JIRA CONCEPTS !!

> WHAT IS AGILE ?
-- Agile is a software development methodology. 
   It has an iterative approach to development. 
   Building and releasing software incrementally from the start of the project, rather releasing all at once in the end. 
   This ierative approach involves planning and developing iteration, implementing the work planned for that iteration and delivering the version of the product by the end. 
   Feedback is then gathered, and used to plan the next iteration. 
   This process continues until the product is fully completed. 
   This process allows the team to adapt the changing requirements. 
   Suppose, If some requirements change as the iterations are relatively short we can manage that in the next iteration. 
   Keeps the development flexible.
   At the end of iteration, we need to deliver a group of features for customer satisfaction, so they can test the features and give feedbacks. 

   Basically, Agile is [ ITERATION PLANNING > IMPLEMENTATION > DELIVERY AND FEEDBACK ] .


> JIRA SUPPORTS TWO AGILE METHODOLOGIES ? 
-- SCRUM 
-- KANBAN 

> WHAT IS SCRUM ?
-- It is a very popular agile methology. 
-- It breaks the project into smaller bits represented by epics and user stories. 
  a> EPIC - It is a larger body of work, broken into stories. 
  b> USER STORY / STORY - It a smallest unit of work. It represents a feature that needs to be developed. 
     For user stories,  usually define a specific format like type of user involved, their golas, and the reason or benefit for that goal. 
     User stories are prioritized. 
     It is continuously implemented and delivered in short cycle , called as SPRINTS. 

> SCRUM FLOW ?
-- It starts of with a product Backlog that contains all the features you want to build in a form of user stories. 
   The features and stories are prioritized and the most important feature or stories will be on the top of the backlog.
   Sprint Backlog basically means these are the features the team will implement during the current sprint. 
   Sprint is basically a pre-determined iteration (usually 2 to 4 weeks) where the development team takes the ticket from the sprint backlog and mark it as done by the end of the sprint. 
   During the sprint, the team will have a daily meeting called as DAILY SCRUM MEETING at a same time and place and discuss the progress and make sure it is on track. 
   Then, the release part comes in the picture, where the features will be released to the customers and they will give us feedback. 


> SCRUM ROLES ?
-- PRODUCT OWNER 
   He/ She basically owns the product.
   In other words,  they defines the vision of the product. 
   They defines what should be built and why. 
   They are responsible for defining what goes into the product backlog. 
   They also creates  the user stories, prioritizes them and make sure it is done. 
-- DEVELOPMENT TEAM 
   They basically builds the product. 
   They are responsible for providing end features at the end of the sprint.
-- SCRUM MASTER 
   They facilitates the scrum process.
   They make sure the team is on track.
   They also make sure there are no blockers for that sprint which would prevent the sprint goal to achieve.


> SCRUM EVENTS ?
-- SPRINT PLANNING
   In this stage, sprint backlog created from product backlog, which means the highest priority feature from the product backlog that the development team can work on during the next sprint.
   Then, the development team will provide their estimate time (story points or hours) needed for that backlog feature. 
   These all plan happens during the Sprint Planning Meeting. 
   Then, the sprint starts. 
-- DAILY SCRUM 
   After the sprint starts, the daily scrum meeting happens with all the members of the team. 
   The meet mainly facilitates by the scrum master. 
   In this meeting, minimum time is limited to 15 mins. 
   The team members what they did yesterday, what are their plans today and do they have any blockers. 
   In case, they have blockers the scrum master steps in and work with them to unblock the blockers they are facing. 
   Scrum call happens everyday for the ongoing sprint. 
-- SPRINT REVIEW 
   After the end of the sprint, reviewing stories which are completed or not completed. 
   And also, to discuss what went well during the sprint and to improve during the next sprint. 



   

   
   
